I’ve been doing a little refactoring. Anyone want to correct me on my mistakes?

Class45 = World

[The int param is a dummy, etc.]

		//aDummyInt147++;
		if (Class22.worldSwitcher != null)
			do {
				try {
					/**
					 * if (i >= -89)
					 *	method92(false, null);
					 * Removed. Reason: dummy.
					 */
					byte[] worldData = Class22.worldSwitcher.readRawWorldList();
					if (worldData == null)
						break;
					Stream worldStream = new Stream(worldData);
					Class27_Sub19_Sub6.totalWorlds = worldStream.method326(-17162); // Total
					Class29.allWorlds = new World[Class27_Sub19_Sub6.totalWorlds];
					for (int curWorld = 0; curWorld < Class27_Sub19_Sub6.totalWorlds; curWorld++) {
						World world = Class29.allWorlds[curWorld] = new World();
						int rawWorldID = worldStream.method326(-17162);
						world.isMembers = (rawWorldID & 0x8000) != 0;
						world.worldID = 0x7fff & rawWorldID;
						world.worldName = worldStream.method302(1995);
						world.playersOnline = worldStream.method338(-7903);
						world.anInt656 = curWorld;
						world.serverLocation = Class27_Sub19_Sub4.method578(false,
								worldStream.method326(-17162));
						System.out.println("Members: " + world.isMembers
								+ ", World ID: " + world.worldID
								+ ", World Name: "
								+ new String(world.worldName.bytes)
								+ ", Players: " + world.playersOnline
								+ ", Location: " + world.serverLocation +" ("+world.getLocation()+")");
					}
					Class99.method1515((byte) 72, 0, -1
							+ Class29.allWorlds.length,
							Class29.allWorlds);
					Class22.worldSwitcher = null;
				} catch (Exception exception) {
					exception.printStackTrace();
					Class22.worldSwitcher = null;
					break;
				}
				break;
			} while (false);
	}

Ahh, and World.serverLocation is an integer that will differ between the values of 0-6. Here are what they stand for (I’m assuming Speljohan didn’t get it) …
